				<div class="postbody">
				Anyone have any insight on Yukos Oil?
<br />

<br />
As I understand it Yukos Oil is held and directed by a man who has been very active in supporting capitalist reforms in the USSR Mikhail Khodorkovsky.  He is also accused of being a robber baron by the socialists claiming that he influanced police and elections.
<br />

<br />
His poliitcal enemies have arrested him and just levied a $99 billion tax levy on Yukos Oil or 107% of their profits.  Yukos Oil closed their doors today and the price of crude in one days trading went up $3 a barrel.
<br />

<br />
Is it safe to invest in Russian companies?  It is prudent to trust Russia in international oil markets at a level where we comingle currency?<br />
