			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Why do we have an SEC?
<br />
What stock scams and swindles went on in the 19th century in the US?
<br />
Why were some folks called <span style="font-style: italic">robber barons</span>?
<br />
Why was there a hereditary rich class in the 19th century in the US?
<br />
What tax, recently repealed, ended the hereditary rich class?
<br />
Why do businessmen in russia/columbia hire bodyguards?
<br />
Why do businessmen in russia/columbia drive around in armored cars?
<br />
What is a potemkin village?
<br />
In how many countries is outright bribery a necessary task needed to stay in business?
<br />
How did accounting firms like Arthur Anderson conspire to prevent the marketplace from correcting itself?
<br />
What were <span style="font-style: italic">solvency letters</span> and why did accounting firms charge clients around $500k for them?
<br />
What are certified public accountants supposed to do? And for whom?
<br />

<br />
The SEC was not put into place to provide employment for lawyers, it was, and is, meant to prevent the stock frauds, swindles and manipulation that went on during the 19th century up to the crash that caused the Great Depression. Every rule they put into place is to prevent a reoccurance of something that went wrong at an earlier time. 
<br />

<br />
The russians don't have an SEC that can do anything. The <span style="font-style: italic">invisible hand</span> can't do anything when the marketplace is highly corrupt. Nor can it do anything when the marketplace is being manipulated by organized crime. The <span style="font-style: italic">invisible hand</span> hasn't stopped boilerrooms from pumping and dumping stocks, nor robbing banks, nor doing an enron. It takes law enforcement to stop them. That's what is what Putin is trying to do. Khodorkovsky is making noises that sound promising to you. Yes, you should assume he is a robber baron. Until proven otherwise, you should assume that any rich russian businessman who got his big start after the collapse of the ussr is a robber baron. Are the taxes 107% of an accurate income or a fraudulent income statement? I bet you will find that his taxes would have been around 21% if he had filed accurate tax returns.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
